cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper deals with computer vision and image processing techniques for urban driving scenes. The paper proposes an efficient procedure to augment real images with virtual objects to create realistic composite images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also deals with 3D modeling and rendering techniques for creating virtual objects, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). 

The proposed approach is aimed at improving the performance of object detection and instance segmentation models for autonomous driving, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). 

The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for semantic segmentation and object detection, which falls under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
